# Specification Driven Development Workflow

Before implementing any feature:

1. Read project.mdc
2. Read architecture.mdc
3. Read frontend_specification.mdc
4. Read code_guidelines.mdc

---

Implementation Order

Phase 1

- Project setup
- Routing
- Store configuration
- Shared infrastructure

Phase 2

- Search feature

Phase 3

- Settings feature

Phase 4

- Validation
- Error handling
- Notifications

Phase 5

- Cleanup
- Refactoring
- Testing

---

Definition of Done

A feature is complete only when:

- UI implemented
- Redux state implemented
- API integration implemented
- Loading state implemented
- Error state implemented
- TypeScript types implemented
- MUI components used
- Responsive layout verified